03/08/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Authorities announced an emergency situation on the eastern Aegean island of Samos on Monday (August 2nd), evacuating hotels after a forest fire broke out. More than 100 firefighters and volunteers, supported by aircraft and helicopters, fought the flames concentrated in the western part of the island. Local authorities said there was no direct threat to hotels and homes, but people have been evacuated as a precaution. (AP, AFP - 02/08/10) 
